  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      In this study the investigators examine the glottic width and the respiratory flow at rest in
      patients with various lung disease. The investigators postulated that a positive expiratory
      pressure is created through the narrowing of the glottic width in patients with
      hyperinflation.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
